    _Imports.razor — Phase 8.0: the project-wide Razor imports for every
    .razor page in BlazorNative.SampleApp (the 7.1 pattern, new project).

    The Components.Web line is LOAD-BEARING, twice over (the 7.0 spike's
    recorded footgun): bind and event tag helpers are namespace-scoped like
    components, so WITHOUT this @using in scope the compiler emits
    `@bind`/`@onclick` as LITERAL MARKUP with ZERO diagnostics and a green
    build — silently dead on a native shell. See
    src/BlazorNative.Components/_Imports.razor for the long-form note.

    BlazorNative.Components is the LIBRARY namespace — the Bn* components the
    pages compose; the pages themselves live in this project's own
    BlazorNative.SampleApp namespace (in scope implicitly).
    ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*@
